# SmartWorkz PowerStack — Environment Variables Template
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values
# NEVER commit .env to git (it's in .gitignore)

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# LOCAL GPU KEYS (Dhoni, KapilDev — Internal LAN)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Dhoni GPU (Qwen 3.5, DeepSeek R1, Phi4 models)
DHONI_API_KEY=your-dhoni-api-key-here

# KapilDev GPU (Qwen Coder, DeepSeek Coder — fast apply/edit)
KAPIL_API_KEY=your-kapil-api-key-here

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CLOUD FALLBACK (OpenRouter Free Tier)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# OpenRouter API Key (for GPT-OSS, MiniMax, Qwen3, Gemma4, Embeddings)
# Get from: https://openrouter.ai/account/api-keys
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-your-new-key-here

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# 1. Generate your keys:
#    - Local keys: Ask your DevOps/GPU admin
#    - OpenRouter: Go to https://openrouter.ai/account/api-keys → Create new key
#
# 2. Fill in the values above (replace "your-*-here")
#
# 3. Save as .env in the PowerPlay root directory
#
# 4. Continue.dev will load these automatically:
#    - Restart VS Code / JetBrains
#    - Continue will read .env and inject variables
#
# 5. Verify setup:
#    - Open Continue chat
#    - Type: "What models do I have?"
#    - Should respond using Qwen 3.5 (local) or GPT-OSS (cloud)

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SECURITY NOTES
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ⚠️  NEVER commit .env to git
# ⚠️  NEVER share API keys via email/chat
# ⚠️  ROTATE keys if accidentally exposed
# ⚠️  Use strong, random keys (OpenRouter generates them)

# If you accidentally expose a key:
# 1. Go to https://openrouter.ai/account/api-keys
# 2. Click the key's menu → "Revoke"
# 3. Generate a new key
# 4. Update .env
# 5. Done!

